But when she watched video of Friday’s Christchurch mosque massacre, she was struck by the green prayer carpet on which the victims lay.
Violent attacks on mosques are rare in France, but the atmosphere often feels hostile to Muslims, Mr. Henniche says.
There has been a recent surge in the number of reported incidents and in their level of aggression, says Mr. Mughal, TellMAMA’s founder.
“A combination of all these elements has created the perfect storm,” Mr. Mughal says.
“Sadly, I think it is only a matter of time before there is another one like that,” Mr. Mughal says.